# Personal deliberation state — the ENTIRE .consilium/ directory is local-only
# (runs, feedback journal, audit state, scratch bundles, screenshots). Ignore it
# wholesale except the single tracked placeholder, so no scratch file can leak
# via `git add -A`. Schema in docs/runs-schema.md.
.consilium/*
!.consilium/runs/
.consilium/runs/*
!.consilium/runs/.gitkeep
FEEDBACK.md
FEEDBACK.html
*.md.bak

# Claude Code session metadata (permissions, local settings)
.claude/*
!.claude/settings.json
!.claude/skills/

# Local bug tracking / agent reports
BUGS.md
bugs-agent-*.md

# Local plans and experiments
# superpowers writing-plans / executing-plans artifacts — personal planning
# scratch (local absolute paths, insider detail); kept on disk, never published.
docs/superpowers/plans/
docs/superpowers/specs/
# TODO.md — internal dev roadmap / bug-audit records / deferred-item notes. Same
# class as the superpowers plans above: planning scratch with insider detail,
# kept on disk but not published. (History still contains it — full scrub is the
# separate clean-public-history task.)
TODO.md
experiments/New phase senat/
.tmp_backup/

# Benchmark harness — regenerable run artifacts (analog of runs/), local only
benchmark/workspace/
benchmark/files/
benchmark/runs/
benchmark/FEEDBACK.html
# Generated report embeds oracle answer values (analyze.py output) — regenerable, never commit
benchmark/report.html
# Answer keys live ONLY in the EXTERNAL sibling Benchmark-scoring/ repo.
# Never commit a scoring tree inside benchmark/ — it would defeat the blind benchmark.
benchmark/scoring/
benchmark/Benchmark-scoring/

# Source upload for docs/architecture (extracted into docs/architecture/)
Arhitecture.zip

# Personal / scratch files — never publish. Broad class patterns so newly-named
# scratch can't slip in via `git add -A` (verified: no tracked file matches these).
*.pdf
*.pptx
*.ppt
tmp_*
*_tmp.*
scratch/
test_bundle.json
